      {
        "id": "b0546b9187db700772491b0be84561b4857d49bc",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 703,
          "name": "Tian Lee",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "TianL@amdocs.com",
          "username": "TianL"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-07-10 09:38:14.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nIs there a reason the logback.xml was added to src/main/resources? Currently the logback.xml file is a part of the kubernetes config map, so that the logging levels can be configured externally. Will this change prevent that?",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "2a10f65fb054f12eac148fb0f9954fb4de837032",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5040,
          "name": "Dmitrii Puzikov",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "d.puzikov2@partner.samsung.com",
          "username": "dpuzikov"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-07-10 10:35:38.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Patch Set 3:\n> \n> Is there a reason the logback.xml was added to src/main/resources? Currently the logback.xml file is a part of the kubernetes config map, so that the logging levels can be configured externally. Will this change prevent that?\n\nThe main reason I've added it is I thought this file is missed. I see it exists in the other projects. Not sure which config will have higher precedence in case of configMap.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "c16a99d7a1941ce2b71b9f1fd22f3a1a3f64a7c7",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 703,
          "name": "Tian Lee",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "TianL@amdocs.com",
          "username": "TianL"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-07-10 11:04:04.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Patch Set 3:\n> \n> > Patch Set 3:\n> > \n> > Is there a reason the logback.xml was added to src/main/resources? Currently the logback.xml file is a part of the kubernetes config map, so that the logging levels can be configured externally. Will this change prevent that?\n> \n> The main reason I've added it is I thought this file is missed. I see it exists in the other projects. Not sure which config will have higher precedence in case of configMap.\n\nI think once Spring Boot has initialised, it will use the logback in the config folder, since it is configured to do so in application.properties:\n\n    logging.config=${CONFIG_HOME}/logback.xml\n\nHowever, any logging that happens before Spring Boot initialisation will pickup the logback from the classpath, so the one in src/main/resources will be used.\n\nIt might be worth making this clear in a comment for example in your logback.xml, that it is not the main one and is only used during Spring Boot initialisation; so that users don't naively update it expecting their changes to take effect.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
